\begin{itemize}

  \href{/competition/firehorn/avionics}{\emoji{🔋} Avionics (AV)} The complex

\item
  \href{/competition/firehorn/flight-dynamics}{\emoji{🌊} Flight Dynamics (FD)}
  A team that exploits different simulators and CFD tools to anticipate
  the in-flight vehicle behaviour.
\item
  \href{/competition/firehorn/ground-segment}{\emoji{🧱} Ground Segment (GS)} A
  subsystem dedicated to build most of the ground based systems that
  allow for monitoring and communication with the launch vehicle.
\item
  \href{/competition/firehorn/payload}{\emoji{🧪} Payload (PL)} The payload
  subsystem gets to design a scientific experiment, as well as other
  accessories.
\item
  \href{/competition/firehorn/recovery}{\emoji{🪂} Recovery (RE)} A subsystem
  focusing on the parachute assembly of the vehicle.
\item
  \href{/competition/firehorn/structure}{\emoji{🦾} Structure (ST)} They ensures
  Firehorn's structural integrity and integrates the other subsystems.

  \href{/hyperion/b_class}{\emoji{🔥} Propulsion (PR)} They get to design the
  engine assembly that'll propell Firehorn to supersonic speeds.
